    <a href="https://civmods.com">https://civmods.com</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>
    When you use our desktop application and interact with our API, we automatically collect your IP address solely for
    logging,
    security, and troubleshooting purposes. We do not collect, store, or process any other personal data.
  </p>

  <h2>Analytics</h2>
  <p>
    We use <a href="https://umami.is/">Umami</a> to collect analytics about the usage of our website and services. Umami
    provides completely anonymized analytics, meaning we do not track or store any personally identifiable information
    through this tool.
  </p>

  <h2>Legal Basis for Processing</h2>
  <p>
    We process your IP address under the legal basis of <strong>legitimate interests</strong> (GDPR Article 6.1.f),
    specifically for maintaining
    security, detecting threats, troubleshooting issues, and improving our services.
  </p>

  <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
  <p>
    Collected IP addresses are used exclusively for:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Security monitoring and threat detection.</li>
    <li>Troubleshooting and analyzing usage patterns to maintain and enhance the stability and reliability of our
      services.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Information Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
  <p>
    We do not sell, rent, or disclose your IP address to any third party unless required by law or necessary to comply
    with a legal obligation, protect our rights and property, or respond to security threats.
  </p>

  <h2>Data Retention</h2>
  <p>
    IP addresses logged by our systems are retained only as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined above.
    After this period, IP addresses are securely deleted.
  </p>

  <h2>Security</h2>
  <p>
    We implement appropriate technical and organizational security measures to protect your information from
    unauthorized access,
    alteration, disclosure, or destruction.
  </p>

  <h2>Your Rights Under GDPR</h2>
  <p>
    Under GDPR, you have the right to:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Access and obtain a copy of your data.</li>
    <li>Request rectification or erasure of your personal data.</li>
    <li>Restrict or object to the processing of your data.</li>
    <li>Lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Please contact us if you wish to exercise any of these rights.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to this Privacy Policy</h2>
